WEST NILE VIRUS - ISRAEL (NORTH DISTRICT) (02)
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat 8 Sep 2007
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

Regarding recent cases in Afula, rates of West Nile fever in Israel
have been strikingly similar to those of North America for the last 3
years. (See graph
<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/Israel-wnf.jpg>; Source [of graph]:
<http://www.GideonOnline.com>)
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

[ProMED thanks Steve Berger for this comment.
A map of the Northern District of Israel can be accessed at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/israel.pdf>. - Mod.TY]
